data.name: 0000 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I guess that takes care of most of it.

data.name: 0001 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Damn Haruhi, always leaving a mess for no reason.

data.name: 0003 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Koizumi, is something wrong?

data.name: 0004 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: It is precisely 3 o'clock.

data.name: 0005 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Ah, right…

data.name: 0006 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: According to the Computer Society, the oddity should start right now.

data.name: 0008 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: Nothing seems to be happening. I wonder if that means time doesn't matter?

data.name: 0009 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: If so, that's quite troubling.

data.name: 0010 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: That would mean we have no way of knowing when an abnormal space will form.

data.name: 0011 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: So what you're trying to say is--we can't rule out one suddenly appearing in front of Haruhi.

data.name: 0012 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Precisely.

data.name: 0013 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Then we have to keep her away from here at all costs.

data.name: 0014 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: Y-you're right. We need to hurry and try to find Suzumiya—

data.name: 0017 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Where did she go?

data.name: 0018 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: She mentioned she was heading for the Computer Society.

data.name: 0019 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: In any case, let's head back to the clubroom building.

data.name: 0021 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: ...Wait.

data.name: 0022 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Hm? What's up, Nagato?

data.name: 0023 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: It has begun.

data.name: 0024 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Begun?

data.name: 0025 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: This melody, is that...?!

data.name: 0026 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: As we walked down the hallway, that melody reached our ears.

data.name: 0027 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Without a doubt, it was coming from the place we just were: The music room.

data.name: 0028 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It's almost as if it was waiting for us to leave.

data.name: 0030 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: Eek... Ky-Kyon?!

data.name: 0031 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Asahina, please calm down.

data.name: 0032 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: I-I'm fine... but, that piano sound…

data.name: 0033 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Yeah, I know.

data.name: 0034 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: We were the ones that knew best—nobody was in that clubroom.

data.name: 0035 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: After all, we had searched through it, every nook and cranny.

data.name: 0036 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: We even locked it, I have the key on me right now.

data.name: 0037 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It would have been impossible for someone to get in there.

data.name: 0039 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Be careful.

data.name: 0040 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: The music is dangerous.

data.name: 0041 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Dangerous...?

data.name: 0042 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: You're telling me it's the same song the Computer Society members were playing?

data.name: 0043 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Not exactly, this one has more information concealed in the tune.

data.name: 0044 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Either way, it still means we have to go and stop their performance.

data.name: 0045 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Koizumi, I'm gonna break into the music room.

data.name: 0046 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Do it.

data.name: 0049 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: This is…

data.name: 0050 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: You have to be joking…

data.name: 0051 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I couldn't believe what I was seeing.

data.name: 0052 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The music room we were just in a while ago had completely changed.

data.name: 0053 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It had truly been transformed into an "abnormal space".

data.name: 0054 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: In the room that had become so unrecognizable…

data.name: 0055 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: …there was a piano playing on its own.

data.name: 0057 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: Eeeek!? Ky-Kyon…

data.name: 0058 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It's ok.

data.name: 0059 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: For now, it seems to just be playing music

data.name: 0060 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Or so I said. No matter how you look at it this isn't ok, is it?!

data.name: 0061 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, I thought you said the music room was normal.

data.name: 0063 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I did.

data.name: 0064 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: That is why the structural information can be easily altered by external interference.

data.name: 0065 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: I see, it's that kind of thing, huh?

data.name: 0066 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: What do you mean? Whatever you two realized, don't leave us out of it.

data.name: 0067 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: For example, when we paint a picture, we do so on a blank sheet of paper.

data.name: 0068 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Why might that be?

data.name: 0069 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It's easier to paint freely that way, right? If the page is all messy it's hard to do anything.

data.name: 0070 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: In essence, that is what we mean.

data.name: 0071 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: The perfectly normal space of the music room serves as a nice canvas to that end.

data.name: 0072 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: In other words, that room can be used as a blank sheet of paper. That is somebody's goal.

data.name: 0073 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: In that case, won't we be getting on that somebody's bad side?

data.name: 0074 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: That possibility cannot be ruled out.

data.name: 0076 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: Wh-what should we do…?

data.name: 0077 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Can't you pull off something with your psychic abilities?

data.name: 0078 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Destroying it all at once would have a negative impact on this space… wouldn't it?

data.name: 0079 (415.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Yes.

data.name: 0080 (415.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: So that's how it is…

data.name: 0082 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: U-um… More importantly…

data.name: 0083 (415.ja) MIKURU (みくる)
data.value: What should we do when Suzumiya returns…?

data.name: 0084 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Indeed, that's quite the pressing matter.

data.name: 0085 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Guess we have no choice but send someone to keep her away again.

data.name: 0087 (415.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: In the meantime, we'll just have to deal with this abnormal space.

data.name: 0088 (415.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It really is just one bother after the next…

data.name: 0089 (415.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: About Haruhi.
